						<summary>

						<p>Hero-stone set up near the temple of Bākavva.</p>						

						<p>12th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This inscription registers the death, in a fight, of Hanmana Sūreya-Nāyaka who had obtained the favour of god Brahmayadēva and goddess Kāḷikādēvi. Ruvāri <hi rend="italic">Ivōja</hi> engraved the record. The characters belong to about 12th century A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
